Package model.hero

Class MarioForm

java.lang.Object
model.hero.MarioForm
public class MarioForm extends Object
Defines the possible states in which Mario could be found. Those states are Small, Super, Fire and Star each with its animated sprite.
Version:
1.0.0

  • Method Details

    • getCurrentStyle

      public BufferedImage getCurrentStyle(boolean toRight, boolean movingInX, boolean movingInY)
      Returns the style to be displayed based on the movement direction and currently selected Mario variation. This is based on the frame of a specified sprite state.
      Parameters:
      toRight - If Mario is moving to the right.
      movingInX - If Mario is moving horizontally.
      movingInY - If Mario is moving vertically.
      Returns:
      The frame of the style to be rendered.

    • fire

      public Fireball fire(boolean toRight, double x, double y)
      The Fireball that needs to be rendered when Mario is in its Fire form.
      Parameters:
      toRight - If the Fireball should be shot to the right or not.
      x - The x coordinate from where the Fireball starts travelling.
      y - The vertical coordinate of the Fireball.
      Returns:
      The Fireball object to be rendered, if Mario is in the Fire form.
